IPC coded to the intruded interior back left side of the right front seat back verses CRS shell. With some unknown factors regarding the securement/tightness of the CRS and excursion of the child, there is a high likelihood the CRS moved significantly from initial placement responding to the initial lateral impact. Based on the damage on the child seat (R > L), the lack of appreciable contact evidence to the wings of the CRS, right chest soft tissue injury (mild bruising from car seat strap) and bilateral nature of his facial injuries (indicative of a single point of contact); with the internal harness holding the child down more on the right side causing the chest injury as the child seat likely tipping toward the right and the childs head excursion scuffing left side of the intruded right front seat back (shown in image 2338).
